bond

Class SpyResult<T>

  • Object
    • bond.SpyResult<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of value contained within this SpyResult.

    public abstract class SpyResult<T>
extends Object

    A class used to hold the return values of spy points. This class is inspired by Google Guava's Optional, but differs significantly in that it can hold null values.

    SpyResults have essentially two states: isPresent() == true or == false. If true, this means the spy point returned a value (from a SpyAgent), even if that value was null. You can then use get() to access this value. If false, no value was returned by the spy point, and calling get() will throw an exception.
